-- UAW to own 55 percent of Chrysler stock: report
-- 
-- Tue Apr 28, 2009 11:01am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/28/us-chrysler-sb-idUSTRE53R08T20090428

 

 (Reuters) - The United Auto Workers will eventually own 55 percent of stock in a restructured Chrysler under a deal reached by the two, the WSJ reported on Monday. 

 * Fiat SpA will eventually own 35 percent of a restructured Chrysler - wsj * Under deal, US government and Chrysler's secured lenders together will own 10 percent of restructured Chrysler -wsj * Chrysler to pay $4.587 billion note into VEBA under deal -wsj * Chrysler to pay $300 million in cash into VEBA in 2010 and 2011, and increasing amounts up to $823 million from 2019 to 2023 -wsj * Under deal, VEBA to own "significant" amount of Chrysler stock, allowed to appoint representative to board -wsj * Under deal, UAW and Chrysler agree to suspension of cost-of-living adjustments, new limits on overtime pay -wsj * Under deal, workers to be paid overtime only after they have worked at least 40 hours in a week -wsj * Chrysler estimates Fiat investment is worth $8 billion, to create 4,000 new UAW jobs in U.S. -wsj * Fiat agreed to produce at least one small car in a Chrysler plant in the U.S. -wsj